The paper deals with lattice-reduction-aided detection for MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the complexity reduction achieved by the new complex LLL algorithm, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper proposes a new algorithm for reducing the basis of a complex lattice, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also presents simulation results, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
